[30;1m492 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m493 | [0m[35mThe official `Python Semantic Release Publish Action`_ is a `GitHub Docker Action`_, which[0m
[30;1m494 | [0m[35mmeans at the beginning of the job it will build a Docker image that contains the Python[0m
[30;1m495 | [0m[35mSemantic Release package and its dependencies. It will then run the job step inside the[0m
[30;1m496 | [0m[35mDocker Container. This is done to ensure that the environment is consistent across all[0m
[30;1m497 | [0m[35mGitHub Runners regardless of platform. With this choice, comes some limitations of[0m

[30;1m406 | [0m[35m[0m

  Filename: [33m/python_semantic_release-9.21.0/docs/algorithm.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m181 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m182 | [0m[35mA list of parsed tags takes ``O(number of tags)`` in space. Parsing each commit during[0m
[30;1m183 | [0m[35mthe breadth-first search between ``merge-base`` and the latest tag in the ancestry[0m
[30;1m184 | [0m[35mof HEAD takes at worst ``O(number of commits)`` in space to track visited commits.[0m
[30;1m185 | [0m[35mTherefore worst-case space complexity will be linear in the number of commits in the[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35mrepo, unless the number of tags significantly exceeds the number of commits[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35m(in which case it will be linear in the number of tags).[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m569[0m[34m of [0m[33m710[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m194 | [0m[35m* Parsing each tag - ``O(number of tags)``[0m
[30;1m195 | [0m[35m* Sorting tags by `semver precedence`_ -[0m
[30;1m196 | [0m[35m  ``O(number of tags * log(number of tags))``[0m
[30;1m197 | [0m[35m* Finding the merge-base of HEAD and the latest release tag -[0m
[30;1m198 | [0m[35m  ``O(number of commits)`` (worst case)[0m
[30;1m199 | [0m[35m* Parsing each commit and checking each tag against each commit -[0m
[30;1m200 | [0m[35m  ``O(number of commits) + O(number of tags * number of commits)``[0m

       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m189 | [0m[35m**Time:**[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m191 | [0m[35mAssuming using regular expression parsing of each tag is a constant-time operation,[0m
[30;1m192 | [0m[35mthen the following steps contribute to the time complexity of the algorithm:[0m
[30;1m193 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m194 | [0m[35m* Parsing each tag - ``O(number of tags)``[0m
[30;1m195 | [0m[35m* Sorting tags by `semver precedence`_ -[0m

       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m181 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m182 | [0m[35mA list of parsed tags takes ``O(number of tags)`` in space. Parsing each commit during[0m
[30;1m183 | [0m[35mthe breadth-first search between ``merge-base`` and the latest tag in the ancestry[0m
[30;1m184 | [0m[35mof HEAD takes at worst ``O(number of commits)`` in space to track visited commits.[0m
[30;1m185 | [0m[35mTherefore worst-case space complexity will be linear in the number of commits in the[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35mrepo, unless the number of tags significantly exceeds the number of commits[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35m(in which case it will be linear in the number of tags).[0m

[30;1m83 | [0m[35m    ``LVHF``. This may be the same as ``LVH``.[0m

[30;1m85 | [0m[35m    previous full release. Call this ``level``[0m

       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m54 | [0m[35m    a. If no commit corresponding to the last non-prerelease version is found,[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m       the entire history of the repository is considered. We parse every commit[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m       that is an ancestor of HEAD to determine the type of change introduced -[0m

  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m3. Find the latest non-prerelease version whose tag references a commit that is[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m   an ancestor of ``M``. We do this via a breadth-first search through the commit[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35m   lineage, starting against ``M``, and for each tag checking if the tag[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35m   corresponds to that commit. We break from the search when we find such a tag.[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35m   If no such tag is found, see 4a).[0m
[30;1m51 | [0m[35m   Else, suppose that tag corresponds to a commit ``L`` - goto 4b).[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m12 | [0m[35m~~~~~~~~~~~[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35m* At runtime, we are in a Git repository with HEAD referring to a commit on[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35m  some branch of the repository (i.e. not in detached HEAD state).[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m* We know in advance whether we want to produce a prerelease or not (based on[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35m====================[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mPython Semantic Release supports releases from multiple branches within your Git[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mrepository. You can elect to have a branch or set of branches create releases or[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m`prereleases`_. There are no restrictions enforced on how you set up your[0m
